content.description: The second most left line on the far side of Grizzly Creek starts in the cave, trends up and left, passes through the anchors for Cosmic Rotisserie and pulls the bulge above. The start can stymie.
content.location: On the far side of Grizzly Creek, the second line from the left, the first truly in the tunnel. Starts on  ledge at water level. If you can't see the ledge, the water is too high.

content.description:
Might be the best line out of the cave, might be the best 12 at Grizzly Dome. The right most line on the far side of the creek, 5' to the right of "Out of The Darkness". If you can't see the ledge to start on, the water is too high.

There is a giant loose flake just below the overhang, usually marked well with white x's. Don't touch it.
content.location: On the far side of Grizzly Creek, the right most line leaving the ledge.

content.description: Short and...short. One of 3 lines inside the tunnel on the right (near) side. Only accessible at very low water. This is the right most line in the tunnel, with a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: At very low water, walk down stream into the tunnel. This is the first line you come to, the rightmost.

content.description: Short and...short. One of 3 lines inside the tunnel on the right (near) side. Only accessible at very low water. Slightly harder than JJ 1.
content.location: At very low water, walk down stream into the tunnel. This is the second line you come to, the centermost.

content.description: Short and...short. One of 3 lines inside the tunnel on the right (near) side. Only accessible at very low water.
content.location: At very low water, walk down stream into the tunnel. This is the last line you come to, the leftmost.

climbs.name: Each Year People Are Killed
climbs.fa: John Stanley, Rick Miller, Don Gruber, Tim Loughlin, January 1991

content.description: Named after the classic Red Rocks warning sign. Start on the right and inside the tunnel. Locate a belay bolt. Trend up and left and then back right, clipping 3 bolts before reaching the roof. Clip a far out left 4th bolt, continue up and generally right to the anchor. 11c variation spurs left at the 5th bolt over the mouth of tunnel and has its own anchor.
content.location: Right side of the tunnel across from "Lust"

content.description: Short and hard. Full of strange body positions, and stranger holds.
content.location: Not quite inside the diversion tunnel, on the far side of Grizzly Creek, the first line on the left. Shares anchor with first part of "Out of the Darkness".
